The paper deals with the problem of variable-length lossy source coding, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT). The paper also involves the analysis of both non-asymptotic and asymptotic cases, which suggests that it may belong to the category of computational complexity (cs.CC). The use of entropy-based quantities and code construction suggests that it may also belong to the categories of data structures and algorithms (cs.DS) and machine learning (cs.LG). Finally, the problem of variable-length lossy source coding may have applications in signal processing and communication systems, which suggests that it may also belong to the category of signal processing (cs.SI).
